# Resolved per machine on first `uv run` so the per-platform torch wheel selection
# keeps working (macOS MPS vs Linux CUDA — see README). Committing a lock would pin
# one platform's torch build and override UV_TORCH_BACKEND, breaking the CUDA path.
# Proper universal multi-platform locking is future work (the deferred Linux/CUDA item).
.venv/
uv.lock
__pycache__/
*.pyc
checkpoints/
